                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Convention between <persName>
                           <forename>Godfrey</forename> de
                        <surname>Crokhurst</surname>
                        </persName> and
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, son of the <persName>lady <forename>Mary</forename> de
                        <surname>Brewose</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, dated 27 Nov., <origDate notBefore="1317-07-08" notAfter="1318-07-07">11 Ed. II</origDate>, by which Godfrey
                  leases to William 10 acres and one rood of land in a certain place called
                  Hallecroft in <placeName key="place_102047">Crokhurst</placeName> in the parish of
                     <placeName key="place_102078">Horsham</placeName>, together with a certain way, for five years.
                  [Dated at the end Friday after the feast of St Andrew [1 Dec.], at <placeName role="date" key="place_102047">Crokhurst</placeName>]  . </p>
                  </msItem>
